        {
            "Original": "Multiple-byte data items are concatenations of bytes, from left to right, from top to bottom.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "From the byte stream, a multi-byte item (a numeric in the following example) is formed (using C notation) by: value = (byte[0] << 8*(n-1)) | (byte[1] << 8*(n-2)) | ...",
            "Adjusted": "From the byte stream, a multi-byte item (a numeric in the following example) is formed (using C notation) by: value = (byte[0] << 8*(n-1)) | (byte[1] << 8*(n-2)) | ..."
        },
        {
            "Original": "| byte[n-1]; This byte ordering for multi-byte values is the commonplace network byte order or big-endian format.",
