{
    "4. Handshake Protocol -> 4.2. Extensions -> 4.2.11. Pre-Shared Key Extension -> 4.2.11.1. Ticket Age": [
        {
            "Original": "The client's view of the age of a ticket is the time since the receipt of the NewSessionTicket message.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "Clients MUST NOT attempt to use tickets which have ages greater than the \"ticket_lifetime\" value which was provided with the ticket.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The \"obfuscated_ticket_age\" field of each PskIdentity contains an obfuscated version of the ticket age formed by taking the age in milliseconds and adding the \"ticket_age_add\" value that was included with the ticket (seeSection 4.6.1), modulo 2^32.",
            "Adjusted": "The \"obfuscated_ticket_age\" field of each PskIdentity contains an obfuscated version of the ticket age formed by taking the age in milliseconds and adding the \"ticket_age_add\" value that was included with the ticket (see Section 4.6.1), modulo 2^32."
        },
        {
            "Original": "This addition prevents passive observers from correlating connections unless tickets are reused.",
