{
    "4. Handshake Protocol -> 4.2. Extensions -> 4.2.8. Key Share -> 4.2.8.2. ECDHE Parameters": [
        {
            "Original": "ECDHE parameters for both clients and servers are encoded in the opaque key_exchange field of a KeyShareEntry in a KeyShare structure.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "For secp256r1, secp384r1, and secp521r1, the contents are the serialized value of the following struct: struct { uint8 legacy_form = 4; opaque X[coordinate_length]; opaque Y[coordinate_length]; } UncompressedPointRepresentation; X and Y, respectively, are the binary representations of the x and y values in network byte order.",
            "Adjusted": "For secp256r1, secp384r1, and secp521r1, the contents are the serialized value of the following struct: struct { uint8 legacy_form = 4; opaque X[coordinate_length]; opaque Y[coordinate_length]; } UncompressedPointRepresentation; X and Y, respectively, are the binary representations of the x and y values in network byte order."
        },
        {
            "Original": "There are no internal length markers, so each number representation occupies as many octets as implied by the curve parameters.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "For P-256, this means that each of X and Y use 32 octets, padded on the left by zeros if necessary.",
            "Adjusted": "For P-256, this means that each of the X and Y coordinates uses 32 octets, padded on the left by zeros if necessary."
        },
