        {
            "Original": "We use the term \"signature algorithm\" throughout the text.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "Each SignatureScheme value lists a single signature algorithm that the client is willing to verify.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The values are indicated in descending order of preference.",
            "Adjusted": "The signature algorithm values are indicated in descending order of preference."
        },
        {
            "Original": "Note that a signature algorithm takes as input an arbitrary-length message, rather than a digest.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "Algorithms which traditionally act on a digest should be defined in TLS to first hash the input with a specified hash algorithm and then proceed as usual.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The code point groups listed above have the following meanings: RSASSA-PKCS1-v1_5 algorithms: Indicates a signature algorithm using RSASSA-PKCS1-v1_5 [RFC8017] with the corresponding hash algorithm as defined in [SHS\"\")].",
            "Adjusted": "The code point groups have the following meanings: RSASSA-PKCS1-v1_5 algorithms indicate a signature algorithm using RSASSA-PKCS1-v1_5 with the corresponding hash algorithm."
