            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "ticket_nonce: A per-ticket value that is unique across all tickets issued on this connection.",
            "Adjusted": "ticket_nonce is a per-ticket value that is unique across all tickets issued on this connection."
        },
        {
            "Original": "ticket: The value of the ticket to be used as the PSK identity.",
            "Adjusted": "ticket is the value of the ticket to be used as the PSK identity."
        },
        {
            "Original": "The ticket itself is an opaque label.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "It MAY be either a database lookup key or a self-encrypted and self-authenticated value.",
            "Adjusted": "The ticket MAY be either a database lookup key or a self-encrypted and self-authenticated value."
        },
        {
            "Original": "extensions: A set of extension values for the ticket.",
            "Adjusted": "extensions is a set of extension values for the ticket."
        },
        {
            "Original": "The \"Extension\" format is defined in Section 4.2.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "Clients MUST ignore unrecognized extensions.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The sole extension currently defined for NewSessionTicket is \"early_data\", indicating that the ticket may be used to send 0-RTT data (Section 4.2.10).",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "It contains the following value: max_early_data_size: The maximum amount of 0-RTT data that the client is allowed to send when using this ticket, in bytes.",
            "Adjusted": "The early_data extension contains the following value: max_early_data_size is the maximum amount of 0-RTT data that the client is allowed to send when using this ticket, in bytes."
        },
        {
            "Original": "Only Application Data payload (i.e., plaintext but not padding or the inner content type byte) is counted.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "A server receiving more than max_early_data_size bytes of 0-RTT data SHOULD terminate the connection with an \"unexpected_message\" alert.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "Note that servers that reject early data due to lack of cryptographic material will be unable to differentiate padding from content, so clients SHOULD NOT depend on being able to send large quantities of padding in early data records.",
            "Adjusted": "No change"
        },
        {
            "Original": "The PSK associated with the ticket is computed as: HKDF-Expand-Label(resumption_master_secret, \"resumption\", ticket_nonce, Hash.length) Because the ticket_nonce value is distinct for each NewSessionTicket message, a different PSK will be derived for each ticket.",
            "Adjusted": "The PSK associated with the ticket is computed as HKDF-Expand-Label(resumption_master_secret, \"resumption\", ticket_nonce, Hash.length). Because the ticket_nonce value is distinct for each NewSessionTicket message, a different PSK will be derived for each ticket."
        },
        {
            "Original": "Note that in principle it is possible to continue issuing new tickets which indefinitely extend the lifetime of the keying material originally derived from an initial non-PSK handshake (which was most likely tied to the peer's certificate).",
